# Assembly Code

addi r1, r0, 5<br>
addi r2, r0, 7<br>
add r3, r1, r2<br>
sub r4, r2, r1<br>
addi r5, r3, 10<br>
addi r6, r3, 5<br>
and r8, r1, r2<br>
or r9, r1, r4<br>
slt r7, r5, r6<br>
slti r2, r3, 13<br>
beq r10, r2, 1<br>
addi r10, r10, 1<br>
beq r2, r10, -2<br>
addi r2, r2, 1<br>

# Note that
- All registers' value is 0.
- All the registers in the assembly code above is r0, r1, ..., r#, which correspond to 00001, 00002, 00003, ...... Please not confuse with the regular ones, such as "a0", "v0", "t1"......

# Result

- r1  :5
- r2  :2
- r3  :12
- r4  :2
- r5  :22
- r6  :17
- r7  :0
- r8  :12
- r9  :7
- r10 :2
